HEADWORD: Dagswain
<hw>Dag"swain`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Dag</er>
a loose end?]</ety> <def>A coarse woolen fabric made of daglocks, or the
refuse of wool.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Under coverlets made of
<xex>dagswain</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Holinshed.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

